text.tspan: Day of the year with peak cherry tree blossom in Kyoto, Japan
The vertical axis shows the date of peak blossom, expressed in number of days since 1st January. The timing of the
peak cherry blossom is influenced by spring temperatures. Higher temperatures due to climate change have caused
the peak blossom to gradually move earlier in the year since the early 20th century.
Day of the year with peak cherry blossom
Data source: Multiple sources compiled by Aono (2021)
Note: The twenty-year average is calculated when there are at least five years with data in the twenty year window.
